# ENTERPRISE ISOLATION GUARD
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Files in this directory are PROPRIETARY and belong EXCLUSIVELY to:
#   gitea/skr8tr-enterprise  (remote: enterprise)
#
# They must NEVER be pushed to:
#   github.com/NixOSDude/skr8tr   (public OSS repo)
#   gitea/skr8tr                  (OSS Gitea mirror — origin remote REMOVED)
#
# HOW THIS WORKS:
#   - Already-tracked files (.c/.h) are managed by git normally on the
#     enterprise remote. Git ignores .gitignore for already-tracked files.
#   - NEW files added here will NOT be staged unless you explicitly run:
#       git add -f src/enterprise/<newfile>
#     This prevents accidental staging of new enterprise files.
#   - GitHub pushes MUST use the temp-clone + filter-repo protocol (Law #17).
#     The github remote has been REMOVED from the local repo to prevent
#     direct pushes.
#
# Federation Laws that govern this directory:
#   Law 15: Enterprise Code Isolation
#   Law 16: File Ownership Tagging  (REPO: enterprise in every file header)
#   Law 17: GitHub Push Protocol    (temp clone + filter-repo only)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Block new untracked files from being accidentally staged
*

# But do not ignore this file itself
!.gitignore

# Do not ignore the laws reference doc
!ENTERPRISE_LAWS.md
